<br>
The problem with VS is that it's an easy raid to do, and the wizards you need will flock to help you.  Basically, other people will run your raid for you.  Anyone can sign up, confident that they can just post, &amp; the people they need will join them, even run the raid for them. <p><img src="http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/sadune.jpg" width="315" height="200"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaphdia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saphdia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 1394<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/19/01 1:17:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I Think It's Definitely Time...</span><hr size=1> I don't have too much of a problem with Adun's proposal with a few refined options.  One being something I've said from the beginning and that is to put something in there that makes it so that guilds can't do back to back raids - something along one cycle..big deal so you don't get to go twice in a month...it's better than the current system for VS.  As the server matures, it won't be hard to get 55 plus people into a guild and who knows, one might have way more than the present higher level guilds one day and might be able to dominate for a whole month...prevention is better than reaction to this imo.  And yes I know your comments on this folks, and it doesn't sway me so please spare me the whine <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  hehe or I'll hand you some of my california cheese.  The other option was that there needs to be a clear definition on how this is to be carried out.  Also, address indys more specifically if they are on the list and all of a sudden get guilded..what happens..trial period or no.  This is happening right now - indys are still on the list that are guilded due to &quot;trial periods&quot; - funny..when are those up?  Nothing formal is being said or done or posted.<br>
<br>
I'd also only vote on this if it were being used for VS only.  I think it is too taxing of a system to use on the other spawns/planes. So hope that is made straight in any proposal.  Clear voting guidelines need to be put at the top.  <br>
<br>
As for the timing of voting on it, I think we better chill till April and let the new system be enforced and give Zest some time.  If she says she needs it, then we need to back off and trust her.<br>
<br>
Saph <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufettenmysteblayde.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fetten Mysteblayde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/19/01 2:20:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I Think It's Definitely Time...</span><hr size=1> Adun, <br>
