Once again, why would you or Darkguard support/sponsor my raid? I would be surprised if you actually knew more then maybe 2 of our members or if you have even seen one of our members in the same zone as you. I guess the point I am making is even though you and Spiritslammer would have to work together to do a VS raid you both still have the power, support and wear withall to do it if the current proposal is inacted. The way I see it there is 5-6 guilds that can get a VS raid at the drop of a hat because A) they either have the members or B)know everyone that supports the idea. You make the argument of a 55 druid that soloed the whole way having the right to do a raid or not. Does it really matter if he/she did solo for 55lvls without being guilded? How many of the guilds out there have higher lvl druids that always group? It's a simple fact that druids and necros solo alot whether they be guilded or not due to the mere fact that they are the best soloable classes in game. Don't mistake this as me not wanting to work together to do these mobs after all I am a ranger and soloing is inconcievable unless it's Crushbone green for rangers. I guess maybe it's the wording I have a problem with. To be honest the the idea of having to drum up support and gain sponsors for a raid I want to host smacks of superiority. You know as well as I do that if you don't know the right people you won't get the support you need for your raid. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukraghack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kraghack</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 475<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/19/01 4:39:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I Think It's Definitely Time...</span><hr size=1> <br>
